Several encoding errors (likely U+00DF for 'ss' and U+00FC for 'ü', and U+2020 dagger symbol) were corrected in the text content. The original XML structure showed excessive and irregular nesting of <BIBL> tags, which has been flattened/corrected where the context implied a sequential list of items rather than deeply nested sub-bibliographies (though some original nesting seems intentional for cross-references, I kept structurally nested <BIBL> blocks but ensured siblings are siblings). I also corrected a misplaced <PRICE> tag to <PRIZE> in one instance, and normalized spacing/line breaks for readability. Specifically:
1.  \u221a\u00a7\u221a\u00fc in 'Vernunfft-m\u221a\u00a7\u221a\u00fcige' corrected to 'mäßige' (ß/ü combination cleaned).
2.  \u221a\u00a7\u221a\u00fc in 'Vernunfft-m\u221a\u00a7\u221a\u00fcige' corrected to 'mäßige' (ß/ü combination cleaned).
3.  \u221a\u221a\u2020 corrected to standard period/space or removed where it seemed like noise separating elements.
4.  \u221a\u00fc (ß) used inconsistently: \u221a\u00fc in 'Prei\u221a\u00fc' corrected to 's'.\n5.  \u221a\u00fc in 'gro\u221a\u00fc' corrected to 'ß' (groß).
6.  \u221a\u00fc in final prize entries corrected to 'ß' (e.g., 13. \u221a\u00fc. -> 13. ß.).
7.  The outermost structural element around the list of <BIBL> items seems to be text before the first <BIBL> tag, which I preserved but cleaned up encoding errors for the introductory sentence. The initial text '11. Bey Herrn Daniel Hag dem Buchbinder sind folgende B\u221a\u00bacher, in nachgesetztem Prei\u221a\u00fc zu verkauffen;' was cleaned. The excessive nesting of <BIBL> tags for Lipsius was partially maintained as it seems intentional structure, but the structure around 'Politicorum Libri' was cleaned to list the subsequent titles as siblings under the main <BIBL> tag of that entry, not nesting them under a second <BIBL> tag.
